long.am,ar,bg,bn,de,en,en_AU,en_GB,en_US,es,e:
#Introduction:
Extract WA Contacts Helper is a Chrome extension designed for users who need to manage and export WhatsApp contacts. Whether you are an individual user or a business user, this extension allows you to easily extract and export WhatsApp contacts, group contacts, and contacts you have chatted with, ensuring that important contact information is properly saved and efficiently managed.

#Features:
Multiple Export Formats: Supports saving extracted contact information in various file formats (Excel, CSV, JSON), making data management more flexible and convenient. No more worries about contact data loss or difficulties in finding information.
Group Search Function: Offers a robust group search function, allowing users to quickly locate and find specific WhatsApp groups by name. Significantly enhances efficiency in finding necessary information among a large number of groups.
Batch Processing: Supports extracting and exporting multiple group contact lists at once, enabling users to complete large-scale data organization and saving tasks in a short time, greatly improving work efficiency and convenience.
Simple Interface: Designed with a clean and straightforward interface, making the operation process intuitive and easy to understand. Even first-time users can quickly get started and successfully complete the extraction and export of contacts.

#Use Cases:
Individual Users: Easily back up important WhatsApp contacts, avoiding data loss due to unexpected situations.
Business Users: Efficiently manage and export contact information from business groups, facilitating customer relationship management (CRM) or other business operations.

#Why Choose Extract WA Contacts Helper:
Efficient and Convenient: No complex operations required. Complete the extraction and export of contacts in just a few steps.
Data Security: All extracted and exported data is stored locally, ensuring your privacy and data security.
Continuous Updates: Constantly optimizing and updating features to ensure continuous improvement of user experience and functionality.

#How to Use:
1. Install the Extract WA Contacts Helper extension.
2. Open web.whatsapp.com and log in to your WhatsApp account
3. Open the extension popup on the page and wait for the extension to access your contacts and group information
4. Select the contacts or groups you need to extract, select the extraction options, and select the export format (Excel, CSV, JSON).
5. Click the "Extract" button, wait for the data to be exported, and save the file locally.

#Disclaimer:
This Chrome extension is not endorsed or certified WhatsApp Inc.
This is an unofficial enhancement tool for it.
This software is not to be used against policies of WhatsApp Inc in any manner.
